<p style="font-family:Times New Roman" ><b><p style="color:blue;">Step 1</p></b>

Mark and cut the smooth middle portion of the bottle to give an even edge approx 7.5 to 8 cm (3") above where you want the fluted rim.</p>
                              <br><br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle3.JPG" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 2</p></b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman" >Measure and make straight, evenly spaced cuts all the way around the bottle. Cut the segments in half and then cut each of those in half to make even, thin strips.
<br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle4.JPG" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 3</b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman" >Carefully press and fold all the strips outward to make a level edge all the way around.</p>
<br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle5.JPG" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 4</p></b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman" >Press the bottle upside down on a flat surface to ensure an even edge.</p>
<br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle6.JPG" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 5</p></b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman">Weave the tip of a strip over the next one and under the next two. Fold and crease it so that the tip is at the place shown here by the arrow.</p>
<br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle7.jpg" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 6</p></b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman">Fold and crease the next one the same way, but weave this one over two and under one.</p>
<br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle8.JPG" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 7</p></b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman">SFold the third strip and weave the same as the first one.</p>
<br>
<center>
<img src="images/pltbottle9.JPG" style="width:200px;height:200px;">
</center>
<b><p style="color:blue;">Step 8</p></b>
<p style="font-family:Times New Roman"> Continue around in this pattern until the last three and tuck each one under the next until woven in completely.</p>
<br>
